</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Maintaining high standards of care and safety is paramount in the dynamic and demanding field of health and social care. This requires a workforce that is not only skilled but also well-versed in the latest statutory and mandatory training requirements. The Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF) offers a comprehensive solution, ensuring that health and social care workers have the essential knowledge and skills to perform their duties effectively and safely. In this blog, Rose explores the significance of CSTF Classroom Mandatory Training and Courses, highlighting key facts, definitions, legislation, and best practices.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-b40d" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety Executive (HSE) reported that 1.7 million working people suffered from ill health-related health in 2021/22.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">The Care Quality Commission (CQC) mandates that all health and social care providers must ensure their staff receive adequate training.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Compliance with CSTF can lead to a reduction in workplace incidents and improve patient care outcomes.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-30_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Statutory training</strong> - This is required by law to ensure that employees can work safely and legally.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Mandatory training </strong>- This includes training that an organisation deems essential for its staff to undertake to work safely and effectively.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF)</strong> - A framework developed to standardise statutory and mandatory training across health and social care sectors, ensuring consistency and quality of training.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-39_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-40_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health and social care organisations must comply with various legislative and regulatory requirements, including:

































































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-45_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014 </strong>- These regulations ensure that care providers meet essential quality and safety standards.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Health and Safety at Work Act 1974</strong> - Mandates employers ensure the health, safety, and welfare of their employees.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Care Quality Commission (CQC) Regulations</strong> - CQC requires that care providers ensure their staff are adequately trained and competent.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-52_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-53_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-54_ pf-heading-1-h3">CSTF face to face mandatory training</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-56_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CSTF classroom Mandatory Training is a yearly refresher course for all healthcare professionals, whether part-time, full-time, or agency workers. This course is aligned to the UK Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF) and meets all major framework training requirements.































































